<p>1. While it is true that qia2o 橋 is not commonly used before Han times to refer to a bridge independently, its common use in place names does seem to indicate clearly that the word did mean bridge even in early times described in ZUO. HEGUAN does have 橋梁. The famous granary in ZUO at Ju4qia2o 句橋, I imagine, was not named after a large beam over a well, but rather a bridge.</p>
